<p><a id=3D"Solved Examples" name=3D"Solved Examples"></a></p>
<h2>Solved Examples</h2>
<p><strong>Q.1: If each interior angle is equal to 144=C2=B0, then how many=
 sides does a regular polygon have?</strong></p>
<p><strong>Solution:</strong></p>
<p>Given: Each interior angle =3D 144=C2=B0</p>
<p>We know that,</p>
<p>Interior angle + Exterior angle =3D 180=C2=B0</p>
<p>Exterior angle =3D 180=C2=B0-144=C2=B0</p>
<p>Therefore, the exterior angle is 36=C2=B0</p>
<p>The formula to find the number of sides of a regular polygon is as follo=
ws:</p>
<p><strong>Number of Sides of a Regular Polygon =3D 360=C2=B0 / Magnitude o=
f each exterior angle</strong></p>
<p>Therefore, the number of sides =3D 360=C2=B0 / 36=C2=B0 =3D 10 sides</p>
<p>Hence, the polygon has 10 sides.</p>
<p><strong>Q.2: What is the value of the interior angle of a regular octago=
n?</strong></p>
<p><span style=3D"font-weight: 400;">Solution: A regular octagon has eight =
sides and eight angles.</span></p>
<p><span style=3D"font-weight: 400;">n =3D 8</span></p>
<p><span style=3D"font-weight: 400;">Since, we know that, the sum of interi=
or angles of octagon, is;</span></p>
<p><span style=3D"font-weight: 400;">Sum =3D (8-2) x 180=C2=B0 =3D 6 x 180=
=C2=B0 =3D 1080=C2=B0</span></p>
<p><span style=3D"font-weight: 400;">A regular octagon has all its interior=
 angles equal in measure.</span></p>
<p><span style=3D"font-weight: 400;">Therefore, measure of each interior an=
gle =3D 1080=C2=B0/8 =3D 135=C2=B0.</span></p>
<p><strong>Q.3: What is the sum of interior angles of a 10-sided polygon?</=
strong></p>
<p><span style=3D"font-weight: 400;">Answer: Given,&nbsp;</span></p>
<p><span style=3D"font-weight: 400;">Number of sides, n =3D 10</span></p>
<p><span style=3D"font-weight: 400;">Sum of interior angles =3D (10 =E2=80=
=93 2) x 180=C2=B0 =3D 8 x 180=C2=B0 =3D 1440=C2=B0.</span></p>
